We have "jitters" on one of our swerve bots, and we needed to adjust the steer PID value to eliminate them. The latest CTR firmware and generated code significantly improved the situation. The jitters appear to stem from unusually high friction during the steer mechanism, whereas friction during drive operation is acceptable. Despite this, adjusting the PID parameters helped stabilize the system. The corrected values implemented were:  

public static final double steerGainsKP = 100;  
public static final double steerGainsKI = 0;  
public static final double steerGainsKD = 2.0;  
public static final double steerGainsKS = 0.2;  
public static final double steerGainsKV = 2.66;  
public static final double steerGainsKA = 0;
